oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Photograph of Roy R. Stephens, Co. H, 5th Inf. Regt. and Co. M, 117th Inf. Regt.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Cpl. Roy R. Stephens, Co. H, 5th Inf. Regt. was part of the American Army of Occupation of the Rhineland immediately after the armistice. He is shown riding a large black mule named Black Fred. American forces occupied this area until 1923. Cpl. Stephens has a Third Army patch sewn on his left shoulder. Two small boys are standing in the right rear are dressed in simple clothes of the era.
